Package net.philsprojects.live

Interface Summary
Module<S> A module is a reference to some strategy implementation where the module can hold many strategies and performing swapping of strategies to active.
ModuleListener<S> A listener invoked when module activity has occurred.
Property<T> A property holds a single value used by a strategy implementation.
PropertyListener<T> A listener invoked when a property change has occurred.
PropertySync<T> TODO
PropertyValidator<T> Each property has a single validator to determine whether a change in value can occur.
Strategy<S> A Strategy holds an implementation to some interface (S) and handles changing properties that can affect the implementation live (immediately) or requires the strategy to update the implementation.
StrategyListener<S> A listener invoked when a strategy update has occurred.
 

Class Summary
AbstractModule<S> An abstract implementation of a module with only strategy swapping logic unimplemented.
AbstractProperty<T> An abstract implementation of a Property.
AbstractStrategy<S> An abstract implementation of a Strategy.

StrategyListenerAdapter<S>
